The Western Cape and Gauteng are the only two provinces with higher coronavirus (COVID-19) recovery rates than the other seven provinces. More than half of the people who contracted the coronavirus in the Western Cape and Gauteng have recovered. Gauteng became the COVID-19 epicentre for a second time on the 8th of July after overtaking the Western Cape which has been the epicentre since the 24th of April. According to the daily national figures, the Eastern Cape has  52 058 total confirmed cases which include deaths, active cases, and recoveries and out of these total confirmed cases, the province recorded 32 083 recoveries. The Western Cape’s recovery rate stands at 59 492. Its total confirmed cases are  79 344. Below is a provincial breakdown of COVID-19 cases in SA:  Free State  North West  Gauteng  Mpumalanga  Northern Cape Eastern Cape  Limpopo  KwaZulu-Natal Western Cape COVID-19 STATISTICS IN SOUTH AFRICA sabcnews.com |  SABC News channel | SABC Radio news SOURCE: Department of Health  & ﻿National Institute of Communicable Diseases  CASES GAUTENG WESTERN CAPE KWAZULU-NATAL EASTERN CAPE FREE STATE LIMPOPO NORTH WEST MPUMALANGA NORTHERN CAPE 3333333 5224 3014 4299 1401 UNALLOCATED 0 AS AT 12 ﻿July 2020 686 DEATHS 19 2348 644 280 36 CONFIRMED CASES | 276 ﻿242 DEATHS| 4 079 TESTS  ﻿CONDUCTED | 2 154 391 RECOVERIES | 134 874 ACTIVE CASES | 137 289 79344 103713 52058 22 33 11 9924 (function(d){var js, id="pikto-embed-js", ref=d.getElementsByTagName("script")[0];if (d.getElementById(id)) { return;}js=d.createElement("script"); js.id=id; js.async=true;js.src="https://create.piktochart.com/assets/embedding/embed.js";ref.parentNode.insertBefore(js, ref);}(document));